<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8405725>
    dc:description "Fig. 80. Conus (Splinoconus) queenslandis da Motta, 1984. A. Holotype, between Lord Howe and Lady Musgrave Island, Queensland, Australia, 150 fathoms, 121.6 mm (MHNG 983.576). B. Grand Passage, 283‒270 m depth, 62 mm. C. Off New Caledonia, 155 m depth, 48.4 mm.D. MontMunida, Norfolk Ridge, 270‒293 m depth, 49.2 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-66066). E. East coast, off New Caledonia, 591‒660 m depth, 83.6 mm. F. Canal de l’Havannah, off New Caledonia, 264‒273 m depth, 45 mm (MNHN- IM-2009-31352). G. W Île des Pins, 295‒300 m depth, 86.6 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-66051). H. E New Caledonia, 250 m depth, 69.6 mm. I. Mont Antigonia, Norfolk Ridge, 180‒210 m depth, 27.8 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-66071). J. W Île des Pins, 250‒225 m depth, 87 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-68770). K. Mont Munida, Norfolk Ridge, 140‒277 m depth, 22.3 mm (MNHN-IM-2013-66126). L. Baie du Santal, Loyalty Islands, 120‒250 m depth, 21 mm. M. Radular tooth of specimen D. Scale bars = 10 mm, unless otherwise stated." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8405725/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

